<subSubSection id="DD3D8652C90D34F501C3FC357B847AC1" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="984E22F7E47B748F27F9C8394327DC98" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="56857A7063BB1823239F8172316CC776" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">
An arbitrary combination of letters, ungendered. 
<emphasis id="D8D28BD84D37526607B483608FAEC827" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Other names</emphasis>
: In 
<bibRefCitation id="644968FF892398C03E5DD3F39D1DDA86" author="Maddison, WP" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Arachnology" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" publicationUrl="http://salticidae.org/salticidImages/" refId="B23" refString="Maddison, WP, 2015b. Salticid images. http://salticidae.org/salticidImages/" title="Salticid images." url="http://salticidae.org/salticidImages/" year="2015 b">Maddison (2015b)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<normalizedToken id="9B1E0513D017350F5AEC91477C2E8011" originalValue="WPM’s">WPM's</normalizedToken>
lab notebooks the informal code for this species was 
<normalizedToken id="65B0854D897602E2610542D7DAC52A1D" originalValue="“BVBML”">&quot;BVBML&quot;</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6B10E3350040053B96E3DF2C7353129C" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="DA6F07F31E77802C8E4BC3F1FDF3AB42" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="688A905C39BCCE05F5504A9FDAD8957F" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">
Both embolus and RTA short and simple (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2EAD0BC139E4E52AECB3574C58B11EF6" captionStart="Figures 76–79" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 76 - 79. Indopadilla bamilin sp. nov., male holotype SWK 12 - 1618 76 left palp, ventral view 77 same, retrolateral view of tibia 78, 79 holotype. Scale bars: on palp 0.1 mm; on bodies 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1004.57526.figures76-79" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/487538" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">76</figureCitation>
). Other species with such a short embolus have a distinct TmA (
<taxonomicName id="A97285838B456D1E86B34E8093723643" genus="I." lsidName="I. annamita" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" rank="species" species="annamita">
<emphasis id="D75D9ABC0269DECB8F374ABFF218E923" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">I. annamita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2DCBA3291A5394DA6BDB9985B44B4E2B" genus="I." lsidName="I. kahariana" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" rank="species" species="kahariana">
<emphasis id="8D595797970B68D7B9E88720AF2DE297" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">I. kahariana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="25351510B9193BD57BBAC060722D0ADD" genus="I." lsidName="I. redunca" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" rank="species" species="redunca">
<emphasis id="4023723CDDD54CAA96CDA4DD491B838D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">I. redunca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="B283A18161CFB49E1CF5350802A5648E" genus="I." lsidName="I. sabivia" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" rank="species" species="sabivia">
<emphasis id="ED32FE46853CF5919829CB3B698A4DAB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">I. sabivia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), which seems lacking in 
<taxonomicName id="E848B3DC4BDC6C6931A948A344B03EF6" genus="I." lsidName="I. bamilin" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" rank="species" species="bamilin">
<emphasis id="7CBC203266B6FE26272BEF8FB2997797" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">I. bamilin</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. First legs and body dark. None of the known females is an obvious match for this male in terms of markings or molecular phylogenetic placement, but also the unmatched females have longer copulatory ducts than would be expected for such a short embolus, or have a more dramatic ECP than expected for the simple RTA.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3B15C81723E10A94116E419CBD2CE1DD" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" type="description">
<paragraph id="4C76F4913D4B0499F3260923774E5176" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0DEE25073FD13887E1F0A13C09C4135C" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="E27D7C7BB6374893543FE9788C91CEFB" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Male</emphasis>
(based on holotype, specimen SWK12-1618). Carapace length 2.3; abdomen length 3.0. 
<emphasis id="AB15516044BF8FE5DF7CCCE9A83EC8DC" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Carapace</emphasis>
dark brown, slightly paler around fovea, with a few patches of pale scales on thorax (Figs 
<figureCitation id="B3276B3CA167C8A60D610BB3FC5BB595" captionStart="Figures 76–79" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 76 - 79. Indopadilla bamilin sp. nov., male holotype SWK 12 - 1618 76 left palp, ventral view 77 same, retrolateral view of tibia 78, 79 holotype. Scale bars: on palp 0.1 mm; on bodies 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1004.57526.figures76-79" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/487538" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">78</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9E2C968AF732F605D634A9BEAC82FEF2" captionStart="Figures 76–79" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 76 - 79. Indopadilla bamilin sp. nov., male holotype SWK 12 - 1618 76 left palp, ventral view 77 same, retrolateral view of tibia 78, 79 holotype. Scale bars: on palp 0.1 mm; on bodies 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1004.57526.figures76-79" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/487538" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">79</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="3174878656E1084E9451CF1DB935B3AE" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Clypeus</emphasis>
dark, narrow; status of arthrodial membrane unclear, as chelicerae are somewhat sunken into the prosoma. 
<emphasis id="F2356CA990A7288969119AAB8831BA0C" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Chelicerae</emphasis>
vertical, brown, concave in front and with lateral ridge. Retromarginal teeth at least three, on long ridge. 
<emphasis id="192F8FCC8D9F147355DE43598D332013" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Palp</emphasis>
femur dark; more distal segments pale. Embolus short, undivided (i.e., no TmA; Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D9AE21A9232C519B576A23D3A115945B" captionStart="Figures 76–79" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 76 - 79. Indopadilla bamilin sp. nov., male holotype SWK 12 - 1618 76 left palp, ventral view 77 same, retrolateral view of tibia 78, 79 holotype. Scale bars: on palp 0.1 mm; on bodies 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1004.57526.figures76-79" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/487538" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">76</figureCitation>
). Tibia with dorsal lobe distally (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E677CC8ECA041C7330AF47A48B424E90" captionStart="Figures 76–79" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 76 - 79. Indopadilla bamilin sp. nov., male holotype SWK 12 - 1618 76 left palp, ventral view 77 same, retrolateral view of tibia 78, 79 holotype. Scale bars: on palp 0.1 mm; on bodies 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1004.57526.figures76-79" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/487538" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">77</figureCitation>
). Endite rounded laterally, without corner or lobe. 
<emphasis id="70EE37F4634309B67E8622915B676B5A" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Legs</emphasis>
strongly contrasting between black leg I and pale legs II-IV. First patella entirely black. 
<emphasis id="C3E060572E802A09C76BA6BB446D2B01" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Abdomen</emphasis>
dark red in life, with longitudinal band of pale scales on each side broken as typical for the genus.
</paragraph>
<caption id="E175906B9F08B4BC14AD3FFE789578E0" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1004.57526.figures76-79" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/487538" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" start="Figures 76–79" startId="F7">
